Note: 
------
&& (AND) and || (OR) are used to combine multiple commands, controlling how they execute based on the success or failure of previous commands.

Logical and (&&):
-----------------
syntax: <command1> && <command2> 
observation: command 2 will only run if  command1  is passed  (i.e exit status  of command1 is 0).

example: 
mkdir myfolder && cd myfolder
observation: cd myfolder will only run if mkdir myfolder is successful (i.e., the folder was created without errors)
	
Logical or ( || ):
------------------
syntax: <command1> || <command2>
observation: command2 runs only if command1 fails (exit status is non-zero).

example:
cd myfolder || echo "Directory not found"
observation: echo "Directory not found" will run only if cd myfolder fails (i.e., if the folder doesnâ€™t exist).




